    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Now, let's get started!</strong></p><p>Boil a kettle and heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a generous drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a high heat</p><p>Trim, then slice your<strong> spring onion[s]</strong> roughly</p><p>Trim, then chop your <strong>green beans </strong>in half</p><p>Once the pan is hot, add your<strong> diced chicken thigh </strong>and <strong>ginger & garlic paste</strong> and cook for 6-7 min or until starting to brown</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1609328389895-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1609328389895-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1609328389895-x700.jpg",
